Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer I role with Axon. I bring full-stack engineering experience building production systems across Python, React, AWS, SQL/NoSQL data layers, and AI-enabled workflows, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I built cloud *backend services* and partner *APIs* that translated natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across *1000+ endpoints*, supporting scalable integrations and reducing operational lift for *Professional Services* teams. I also implemented tracing and structured observability with Langfuse and LangSmith to resolve complex integration bugs and streaming issues, then optimized routing and concurrency to meet strict latency requirements and high availability targets in a mission-critical environment (latency -60%, API costs -50%). At Qualitest, I designed integration services across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO with Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis, and delivered full-stack IAM features using React, Sprint Boot, AWS, and Step Functions for 30+ applications. This experience aligns directly with Axon's need for engineers who can own features end-to-end, from services and APIs to frontend components and operational reliability.

I am especially motivated by the Real Time Operations Integrations mission. Building integrations across varied partner systems, including RMS/CAD/LPR-style workflows, mirrors the integration complexity I have worked on and the product mindset I bring to design reviews, sprint planning, and cross-functional delivery with engineering, product, and customer-facing teams. My research and workshop experience at Pace AI Lab also strengthened the technical communication needed to collaborate across disciplines and raise team engineering standards.

Axon's mission to *Protect Life* strongly resonates with me, and your focus on *Preserve Truth* and *Accelerate Justice* is exactly the kind of impact I want my engineering work to support. I would welcome the opportunity to contribute to Axon's goal of protecting more lives in more places and to help the RTO Integrations team deliver reliable real-time systems for first responders and the communities they serve. Thank you for your consideration; I can be reached at #ph or #eml.

